{
  "text": "Domain Specific Modeling (DSM) is a problem-oriented methodology which allows one to exactly specify the specific domain with the concepts and relationships that map closely to the given domain. To provide the computing and execution of these domain models, technologies of model transformations and model anchoring need support the automated generation of pre-implemented models mapped from those domain models. A three-level architecture of DSM, taken from [CITATION_1] , is illustrated in the following figure 2.",
  "citation_candidates": [
